c: 12
v: 66
t: "Yaqoub, (Jacob), their father) said: \"I will never send him with you until you swear a sincere promise to me, in the Name of Allah, that you will be sure to bring him back to me unless you are yourselves surrounded (and powerless).\" And when they had sworn their truest promise, he said: \"To all that we say, let Allah be the Witness and Guardian"